{
  "doc_id": "2733",
  "text": "The term \"cluster analysis\" refers to a group of statistical methods that seek to organize information so that data from heterogeneous variables can be classified into relatively homogeneous groups [CITATION_1] . In recent years, cluster analysis has been used to examine heterogeneity of patients with chronic airway diseases including asthma [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and COPD [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . Cluster analysis is often presented as an unsupervised and unbiased method. However, important aspects related to the different methods of cluster analysis and to the choice of variables included in the analysis may affect the results.",
